= The proposed solution
This new method can act in addition to PD detection by utilising the existing UHF antennas installed in GIS. One antenna is used to set up a standing wave while another is used to monitor the magnitude of the field. Defects moving down the GIS should scatter the standing wave resulting in a changing magnitude. Recording this magnitude over the lifetime of the installation can be used to track changes to the mechanical structure of the GIS and identify defects.

