= Practical Experiment
The practical experiment is conducted using a $1m^3$ metal box. Two experiments were run. In the first experiment, the defect is moved incrementally after opening the box before each measurement. In the second experiment, the defect is pulled through the box using a piece of fishing line. The second experiment records the transient effects of a moving defect.

The output of the NanoVNA shown is the insertion loss in dB, which is the S21 magnitude expressed in decibels.

#figure(
  image("images/NanoVNARec.png", width: 15cm),
  caption: [The S21 parameter against defect position recorded with the NanoVNA. ],
) <nanoVNA>

@nanoVNA shows the S21 parameter recorded with the NanoVNA against defect position. The defect is a cylinder of diameter $76.2 "mm"$ with a height of $20 "mm"$.


