= Conclusion
The simulations show the influence of defects on the magnitude of the standing wave and the resulting sinusoidal output. These results are shown to be similar in the metal box simulation. Practical experiments show that the NanoVNA is able to detect a large defect through the cube with the same output characteristics as the simulations.

In the simulations, the sensitivity was shown to be dependant on the particle size and how close the defects moved to the antinodes. This may potentially limit the applications of this approach for the protrusion type of defects.

This project focussed on testing a simple GIS busbar and has not simulated complex GIS structures. Future work should test more complex geometries with practical sections of GIS.



